/*
There are mainly Three types of scope:-
1)method scope:-

function to variable
-> can use variable in function
-> variable declared in function cannot be used in main

example:-

  public static void hello{
  int s=10;
  System.out.println("Hello");
  System.out.println(s);    // s is declared first
  }
  public static void main(String args[]{
  System.out.println(s);             // this will give an error because we cannot use variable in main function which is used in the function 
  }
  
  
2)Block scope:-

    {
        |
    Block od code
        |
    
    }
    
    example:-
    public static void main(String args[]){
    int p=10;               //p block starts
    {
      {                     // s block start
      int s=45;
      System.out.println(p);    // no error inside the block
      }                     //s block end  
     System.out.println(s);   // show error outside the block
     System.out.println(p);    // no error inside the block
    }
*/

/*
3) class scope:-
   these are those scope we use comminly in Java coding 
    ->public
    ->protected
    ->private
*/
